div.p:
—establish a new Office of Personnel Management (OPM) to supervise and direct the management of executive branch
                    personnel, and to issue Government-wide personnel regulations, with authority to
                    delegate certain personnel authorities to the agencies;

—establish a new performance appraisal program, and new standards for dismissal
                    based on unacceptable performance and suspension based on a pattern of
                    discourteous conduct to the public;

—create a Senior Executive Service as a distinct personnel system with special
                    procedures for selection, development and pay of high-level Federal
                    managers;
